All Implemented Interfaces:
java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible
public class ClientApplication
extends javax.swing.JPanel

GUI - Client application class for Rock-Paper-Scissor
firstly, user must set his name - board becomes visible
after that user can make his move and waits his opponent
user can also to view list of all participants names - players and spectators
after the end of the game - user can choose new game option

Constructor Detail

ClientApplication

public ClientApplication()
Create a socket to communicate with a server on port 8080 of the host that the applet's code is on. Create streams to use with the socket. Then create a TextField for user input and a TextArea for server output. Finally, create a thread to wait for and display server output.
